# TypeScript Standards

## Imports

- Use `type` for type-only imports: `import type { X } from '...'`
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Order: external libs first, then internal (di, hooks, ui, theme, types)

## Types

- Define shared DTOs in `src/types/index.ts`
- Use `interface` for object shapes; `type` for unions/aliases
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` and narrow if needed

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (e) {}

// ✅ GOOD
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (e) {
  // Log or rethrow with context
  throw new Error('Failed to fetch', { cause: e });
}
```

## Naming

- Use cases: `XxxUseCase` (e.g. `ObserveTimeStateUseCase`)
- Repositories: `IxxxRepository` (interface), `MmkvXxxRepository` (impl)
- Hooks: `useXxx` (e.g. `useObserveTimeState`)
- Screens: `XxxScreen` (e.g. `HomeScreen`)
